headline: Updated Preliminary Agenda: 5th Palm Beach CorpGov Forum Nov 5-6
summary: CorpGov, IPO Edge and PE Edge will host the fifth annual Palm Beach CorpGov Forum on Wednesday, Nov. 5 and Thursday, Nov, 6, 2025, at the Palm Beach Lake Pavilion, located waterfront with sweeping views of Palm Beach Island. headline: Nestle Leaves Climate Alliance for Dairy Emission Reductions
summary: Nestle was a founding member of the international group started at the 2023 UN climate conference, alongside Kraft Heinz, Starbucks, Danone and General Mills.

headline: Will Kraft Heinz's (KHC) Canada Sports Push Reinforce Its Competitive Edge in Brand Loyalty?
summary: Kraft Heinz Canada and Maple Leaf Sports & Entertainment recently announced a new multi-year partnership, bringing HEINZ ketchup and mustard back to MLSE venues across Canada, including Scotiabank Arena, starting with the 2025-2026 NHL season. This move responds to more than six years of fan demand, introducing innovative condiment stations and reaffirming HEINZ as a core part of the Canadian live sports experience. We'll examine how Kraft Heinz's renewed presence in major Canadian venues...

headline: Does Kraft Heinz’s Recent Partnership Signal a Rebound Opportunity in 2025?
summary: If you’ve been debating what to do with Kraft Heinz stock lately, you’re certainly not alone. It’s one of those familiar names that always seems to attract attention, especially when its performance takes a turn. Kraft Heinz shares have been on a slide this year, down 17.4% year-to-date and down 22.5% over the past twelve months. Over the longer run, though, the drop isn’t quite as steep, with a milder 1.4% decline over five years. These numbers might make it feel like the risk profile around...
